org.apache.taverna.server.localworker.remote

Interface RemoteDirectoryEntry

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Remote
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    RemoteDirectory, RemoteFile
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DirectoryDelegate, FileDelegate

    public interface RemoteDirectoryEntry
extends Remote
    An entry in a RemoteDirectory representing a file or sub-directory.
    Author:
    Donal Fellows
    See Also:
    RemoteDirectory, RemoteFile

    • Method Detail

      • getName

        @Nonnull
String getName()
                 throws RemoteException
        Returns:
        The "local" name of the entry. This will never be ".." or contain the character "/".
        Throws:
        RemoteException - If anything goes wrong with the communication.

      • getModificationDate

        @Nonnull
Date getModificationDate()
                           throws RemoteException
        Returns:
        The time when the entry was last modified.
        Throws:
        RemoteException - If anything goes wrong with the communication.

      • getContainingDirectory

        @Nullable
RemoteDirectory getContainingDirectory()
                                          throws RemoteException
        Gets the directory containing this directory entry.
        Returns:
        A directory handle, or null if called on the workflow run's working directory.
        Throws:
        RemoteException - If anything goes wrong with the communication.

      • destroy

        void destroy()
      throws RemoteException,
             IOException
        Destroy this directory entry, deleting the file or sub-directory. The workflow run's working directory can never be manually destroyed.
        Throws:
        RemoteException - If anything goes wrong with the communication.
        IOException - If things go wrong when deleting the directory entry.
